line_1: Moss creeps below, and waxen fruit impends.
line_2: Round wiry stems the flaxen tendril bends,

line_1: Its marble arms, and high in air impends;
line_2: Wide o'er the deep a dusky cavern bends

line_1: Ah! blind to fate! the storm impends,
line_2: That blights thy hopes, destroys thy friends;
